      <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b>, waived when you authorize the repair</li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar"><div class="wrap"><span>BHGS #A49573 · Insured</span><span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span><span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span></div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Frigidaire, Electrolux-owned value-to-mid-market tier</h2>
    <p>Frigidaire has been owned by Electrolux AB (Stockholm-based Swedish parent) since 1986. Within Electrolux's North American brand hierarchy, Frigidaire occupies the value-to-mid-market tier, below Electrolux mainstream and Electrolux Icon Professional, but above entry-tier generic brands. The shared Electrolux parent gives Frigidaire service access to substantial parts commonality with comparable Electrolux wall oven models, bake elements, broil elements, thermostats, convection fan motors, door hinges, and many control-board variants interchange between mainstream Electrolux and mainstream Frigidaire. This parts commonality strengthens parts-supply availability and reduces lead times on common service items.</p>
    <p>Frigidaire's own three-tier wall oven lineup, Professional (top, pro-style visual $1.4-2.2k), Gallery (mid, improved features $900-1.6k), mainstream (base $600-1.2k), runs through Electrolux-Frigidaire distribution with typical 2-4 day lead on common parts.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Frigidaire wall oven models we service</h2>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Frigidaire mainstream 30" built-in</h3><p>Base value-tier wall oven. Practical bake + broil + self-clean. Service: bake/broil element, convection fan (where equipped), control board, sensors, door hardware.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Frigidaire Gallery 30" built-in</h3><p>Step-up tier with convection on most models. Better control platform + finish quality than mainstream.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Frigidaire Professional 30" built-in</h3><p>Pro-style top tier with heavier construction + True Convection variants. Advanced features + heavier-spec components.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Frigidaire 30" double wall oven</h3><p>Stacked dual-cavity across mainstream + Gallery + Professional tiers. Per-cavity service patterns.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Electrolux parts commonality</h3><p>Mainstream Frigidaire wall oven parts interchange substantially with mainstream Electrolux at the chassis level. Combined parts-supply pool improves availability.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Self-clean pyrolytic cycle</h3><p>Standard self-clean across Frigidaire tiers. Door-lock motor + thermal sensor + cycle firmware service.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Common Frigidaire wall oven faults</h2>
    <p><b>Bake or broil element failure</b>, 8-12 year typical on Frigidaire mainstream; slightly longer on Gallery/Professional tiers. $200-$360 per element.</p>
    <p><b>Convection fan motor wear (Gallery/Professional)</b>, $260-$440.</p>
    <p><b>Control board lockout</b>, factory reset resolves some; replacement $340-$580.</p>
    <p><b>Temperature sensor drift</b>, $160-$300.</p>
    <p><b>Door hinge wear</b>, $200-$340.</p>
    <p><b>Self-clean door-lock motor</b>, $200-$360.</p>
